  "timeboxMinutes": 25,
  "prompt": "The trips endpoint is paginated and may rate-limit you.\n\nWrite `fetch_all_trips(base_url, token)`. Return every trip dict from `GET {base_url}/v1/trips`, in API order. If a request returns `429`, read the `Retry-After` header, wait that many seconds, and retry the same request.\n\nReturn contract:\n\n- Return `list[dict]`.\n- Each dict should be one trip object from the API, unchanged.\n- Do not return a response object, status code, or nested `{\"data\": ...}` wrapper.\n- Return `[]` if there are no trips.\n\nTrip shape:\n\n```python\n{\"id\": \"trip_001\", \"employee_id\": \"emp_001\", \"destination\": \"SFO\", \"start_date\": \"2026-04-01\", \"end_date\": \"2026-04-03\", \"total_cost_cents\": 120000}\n```\n\nEndpoint details:\n\n- `GET {base_url}/v1/trips` requires the bearer auth header.\n- Success response: `{\"data\": [...], \"next_cursor\": \"...\" | None}`.\n- Rate-limit response: `status_code == 429`, `headers[\"Retry-After\"]` is a string number of seconds.\n\nThe test harness passes `token` into your function. Do not define or hardcode it; use the `token` parameter when building the `Authorization` header.\n\nInvariants and corner cases:\n\n- A `429` has no page data. Do not advance the cursor or append anything after a `429`.\n- Retry the same URL/params after a `429`.\n- Do not sleep between every successful request; only back off when rate-limited.\n- Preserve order and avoid duplicates.\n\nShared fake API note: this uses the in-process `requests` mock described in the Ramp Travel module guide; there is no real network.\n\nValidation focus: auth, pagination, first-page and later-page 429s, and retrying the same cursor.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "fetchAllTrips",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "base_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "token",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "any"
      }
    }
  },
